				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Upgrading Gear, need suggestions for arm slot.<a name="46082"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 15 04 8:38 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>ornate &gt; heraldic, I dont doubt that. I go by hp - stam - mana - cha - int - dext - agil when I upgrade, assigning points like in the upgrade guide to different stats. Raw hps I assign 4 points, stam is 3, cha is 3, int is 3, dext is 2, mana is 3, agil is 2, each resist is 2, and each point of ac is 1. 
<br />

<br />
When I upgrade I compare totals on one item to another. If the totals are within 10-15 points of each other its probably not worth the upgrade. Anyhow, ornate is a good upgrade over fierce. Mir is not within upgrade range from ornate but I woulda gotten more HPs with Mir.
<br />

<br />
Edit: This is the <a target="_new" href="http://www.eqdiva.com/EQ/Guide.aspx?id=49&amp;ForumID=132">guide</a> I was talking about. Written by sapper a ways back, I adapted his idea of assigning point values using hp as a base to assigning a generic point value.</span></td>
